## The Good News
The error `EADDRINUSE: address already in use :::3001` means:
- âœ… Your environment variables are working correctly
- âœ… The backend script is functioning properly  
- âœ… There's already an API server running on port 3001
- âœ… You can now use the API to create users!

## Solutions (Choose One)

### Solution 1: Use the Running API Server (Easiest)
```bash
# Use the existing API server to create users
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/create-admin-user \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "x-api-key: benirage-admin-2024"
```

### Solution 2: Find and Kill the Running Server
```bash
# Find the process using port 3001
lsof -ti:3001

# Kill the process
kill -9 $(lsof -ti:3001)

# Then run the script again
node scripts/utils/create-admin-simple.js
```

### Solution 3: Use Alternative Port
```bash
# Kill the current server and restart on a different port
kill -9 $(lsof -ti:3001)

# Set a different port and run
PORT=3002 node scripts/utils/create-admin-simple.js
```

### Solution 4: Direct Admin Creation (No Server)
```bash
# Go to backend and use direct mode
cd backend
node -e "
const { createUsers } = require('./create-admin-user.js');
createUsers().then(() => {
  console.log('Users created successfully!');
  process.exit(0);
}).catch(console.error);
"
```

## Recommended: Use Solution 1 (API Method)

Since you already have a server running, Solution 1 is the quickest:

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/create-admin-user \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "x-api-key: benirage-admin-2024"
```

This will create all 5 admin users through the existing API server!

